Description: Lip sherd (mended from two fragments) of Milesian Fikellura pottery trefoil oinochoe; white slip; interior: top of rim glazed, plus black splash; exterior black, flaking off; possible traces of white outline of eye; part of moulded ridge at junction with neck.
Curator's comments: Sherd probably belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1886,0401.1051 and 1924,1201.922 (shown joined in CVA BM 8, pl. 9 no. 2 and Walter-Karydi 1973, pl. 2, 24, but now detached).
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (9, no. 2)
Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 248, no. 6)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.159)
